This paper discusses the Cactus Framework, which is a programming environment for scientific applications using high-performance computing. The paper focuses on the sustainability of the software, which suggests that it may fall under the categories of cs.MS (Mathematical Software), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.SE (Software Engineering), cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), and cs.PF (Performance).
